{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-template-tsx","path":"/blog/Adding-Slide-Numbers-to-MDX-Deck-Presentations/","result":{"data":{"contentfulBlogPost":{"createdAt":"July 26th, 2020","title":"Adding Slide Numbers to MDX Deck Presentations","heroImage":{"fluid":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/c3b73bxvesf2/42sodhiJnAFQGMUcOVi8x8/4068692347bac6d75ce20ca10b401d29/photo-1512314889357-e157c22f938d?w=800&q=50"}},"body":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>MDX Deck is a fast and lightweight library that lets you write presentations in markdown. More specifically, it uses <a href=\"https://github.com/mdx-js/mdx\">MDX</a>, an extension of markdown that allows you to use JSX and React components. This allows you to do cool things like import React components into your slide deck and interact with them.</p>\n<p>First, follow the <a href=\"https://github.com/jxnblk/mdx-deck#getting-started\">Getting Started</a> instructions in the README of MDX Deck.</p>\n<p>You should end up with the following file structure:</p>\n<pre><code>.\nâ”œâ”€â”€ node_modules\nâ”œâ”€â”€ deck.mdx\nâ”œâ”€â”€ README.md\nâ”œâ”€â”€ package.json\nâ”œâ”€â”€ package-lock.lock\n</code></pre>\n<p>Then create a <code>&#x3C;Layout></code> component:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx\">// layout.js\n\nimport React from \"react\";\n\nconst Layout = ({ children }) => {\n  return (\n    &#x3C;>\n      &#x3C;div>{children}&#x3C;/div>\n      &#x3C;footer>\n        &#x3C;span>My Awesome Presentation! ðŸš€&#x3C;/span>\n        &#x3C;span>@corrinachow&#x3C;/span>\n      &#x3C;/footer>\n    &#x3C;/>\n  );\n};\n\nexport default Layout;\n</code></pre>\n<p>You can now create slides in your <code>deck.mdx</code> file with the <code>Layout</code> component where the slide contents will render as <code>children</code>.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-md\">// deck.mdx\n\nimport Layout from \"./Layout\";\n\n&#x3C;Layout>\n\n# My Awesome Presentation! ðŸš€\n\nCorrina Chow\n\n&#x3C;/Layout>\n</code></pre>\n<p><img src=\"https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/i/nlkh0fenwngqd1xj6dud.png\" alt=\"MDX presentation with footer\"></p>\n<figcaption>MDX Deck slide with footer using a Layout component</fixcaption>\n<p>This is useful for making headers, footers or layouts for your slides.</p>\n<p>Now if you dig into the source code, you'll see that MDX Deck uses a React Context called <code>useDeck</code> to pass deck data between components. This includes the index of the slide, speaker notes, or presentation mode!</p>\n<p>This hook happens to be exported from the library and can be used to your advange.</p>\n<p>In <code>layout.js</code> file, import the <code>useDeck</code> React hook from <code>mdx-deck</code>. There's a property represents index of the slide you're viewing. From that, you're able to extract slide numbers and add it to your presentation ðŸ¥³</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx\">// layout.js\n\nimport React from \"react\";\nimport { useDeck } from \"mdx-deck\"; // Import useDeck\n\nconst Layout = ({ children }) => {\n  const state = useDeck(); // Declare a new state variable\n\n  const currentSlide = state.index + 1; // The slides are zero-index\n  return (\n    &#x3C;>\n      &#x3C;div>{children}&#x3C;/div>\n      &#x3C;footer>\n        &#x3C;span>My Awesome Presentation! ðŸš€&#x3C;/span>\n        &#x3C;span>{currentSlide}&#x3C;/span>\n        &#x3C;span>@corrinachow&#x3C;/span>\n      &#x3C;/footer>\n    &#x3C;/>\n  );\n};\n\nexport default Layout;\n</code></pre>\n<p><img src=\"https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/i/xg2hmzcxqnkj7mm775r4.png\" alt=\"MDX Deck with slide number\"></p>\n<figcaption>MDX Deck with slide number!</fixcaption>\n<p>There's a bunch of other values that can be accessed with the <code>useDeck</code> context, such as the <code>length</code> of the presentation, or HTML <code>head</code> values. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/i/cdvqlvxqqnggdemh97gc.png\" alt=\"useDeck props\"></p>\n<figcaption>useDeck properties</fixcaption>\n<p>Hope this was helpful ðŸ˜„</p>\n<h2>References</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://reactjs.org/docs/context.html\">React Context</a>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/mdx-js/mdx\">MDX Docs</a>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/jxnblk/mdx-deck\">MDX Deck</a></p>"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"Adding-Slide-Numbers-to-MDX-Deck-Presentations"}}}